<br>
I hate to say but dang it most mages and other classes need to have a trial of driving or something before they can't unlock the pets sheesh.<br>
<br>
Mulk  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=merlankinthepunted>MerlankinThePunted</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#333333>(1/23/03 3:50:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Non Magicians learn your pets!!</span><hr size=1> I agree.  Alot of classes don't know jack about pets... even some mages.  Pets push like a motha, and everyone should learn that.... Most fights I try and control the push, but setting my pet in certain positions.... though running too close to the mob can get ya wacked a couple times <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
