</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eloinapyromancer>Eloina Pyromancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 358<br> <font color=#333333>(1/27/03 8:59:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Non Magicians learn your pets!!</span><hr size=1> God, I am so sick of raid leaders without a clue about pets.<br>
<br>
We have one particular raid leader who is convinced that if anything bad happens, it was a pet's fault.  To the point that I refuse to go on raids with her anymore.<br>
<br>
Last raid I went on with her was in PoG.  The puller agroed some caster mobs while bringing in the pull, and instead of rushing right in, they stood around and nuked for awhile before charging.  Of course, that gave them opportunity to bring more friends, so the ending train was pretty big.<br>
<br>
So, we wiped.  And her immediate response was to ban all pets.<br>
<br>
I argued with her for awhile, but then got disgusted with the whole thing, disbanded and gated out.  Call me immature, but I'd had enough of her attitude.<br>
<br>
So now, I lead groups of 5 mages/necros and 1 shaman into PoG and we take all of the trash in the zone, as well as some of the lesser nameds.  Great loot, great cash, ok xp, and lots of fun. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tevzia>TevZia</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#333333>(1/28/03 10:42:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Non Magicians learn your pets!!</span><hr size=1> There are some places where using pets just isn't a good option. And, I trust my raidleaders if they say no pets, it's rare, but it happens.<br>
<br>
With PoP some Mobs have god awful AEs that will eat pets in no time. And regular mobs hit so hard that if you are 1 second late with backing pets off at Enrage they die.<br>
<br>
The best thing though, is to kill pet when told so, and argue afterwards, however sucky wrong the raidleader is.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lordgojirax>LordGojirax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 369<br> <font color=#333333>(1/28/03 6:47:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jackntracie.com/images/gojhead.jpg width=98 height=126></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Non Magicians learn your pets!!</span><hr size=1> Without /pet hold, I know a good number of zones that I wouldn't allow pets in.<br>
<br>
Trak raids for instance. I've known trak to aggro pets with his dragon roar and AoE. (Even if it doesn't hit.)<br>
<br>
Places where pathing is AWEFUL where you can be standing 5 feet from a mob and send your pet, then watch him run a few laps around a building then enter it from the back and pull a few adds while he's at it. (Like 2nd floor of Hate.)<br>
<br>
While I agree that Non Mages/Pet Classes should learn about pets. On the same token, pet classes should also take the time to learn their zones and mobs. If you aren't a MASTER at a zone, then perhaps trust the raid leader.<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.jackntracie.com/images/gojirax.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eloinapyromancer>Eloina Pyromancer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 366<br> <font color=#333333>(1/29/03 4:33:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Non Magicians learn your pets!!</span><hr size=1> I'm not a newbie.  I played a mage at release, when it was tough for pet classes.  Bad pathing?  Yeesh, the pathing in dungeons the first year was so bad that it was almost funny.<br>
<br>
So yes, if the raid leader has a clue about what they're talking about, I'm happy to listen to them.  If I don't know the zone, the mob, or the pathing I'm happy to kill off pets until I do.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, when they don't have a clue (as in the example raidleader I mentioned above), I refuse to put up with the bullshit anymore.  <br>
<br>
Do you know what 4 years of EQ means?  Way too many raidleaders who think they are God's answer to the masses.<br>
<br>
Life's too short. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lordgojirax>LordGojirax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 376<br> <font color=#333333>(1/29/03 4:47:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jackntracie.com/images/gojhead.jpg width=98 height=126></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Non Magicians learn your pets!!</span><hr size=1> Another reason I try to avoid pickup raids <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.jackntracie.com/images/gojirax.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zarroslivinglight>ZarrosLivinglight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#333333>(1/30/03 3:25:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=412.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Non Magicians learn your pets!!</span><hr size=1> Raid leader shouts &quot;Back off pets&quot;<br>
mages dutifully back their's off<br>
necromancers dutifully back their's off<br>
enchanters dutifully back their's off (gogo charm or aa's)<br>
beastlords dutifully back their's off<br>
shadow knights dutifully back their's off<br>
druids dutifully back their's off<br>
main tank and assist tanks back off<br>
